-- Kiel Institute May Raise German Economic Growth Forecast, Berliner Says
-- Jana Randow
-- 2010-08-06T06:05:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-06/kiel-institute-may-raise-german-economic-growth-forecast-berliner-says.html

          
          
             The Kiel-based Institute for the
World Economy may raise its German economic growth forecast from
2.1 percent this year on increasing export demand, Chief
Economist  Joachim Scheide  told  Berliner Zeitung .  
 “We might very well revise up our forecast again,”
Scheide told the newspaper. “In contrast to other countries,
Germany is in an exceptional situation. The German economy is
doing incredibly well.”  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
